.TH "q6asm_map_memory_regions" 9 "q6asm_map_memory_regions" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
q6asm_map_memory_regions \- map memory regions in the dsp.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" q6asm_map_memory_regions
.BI "(unsigned int dir "  ","
.BI "struct audio_client *ac "  ","
.BI "phys_addr_t phys "  ","
.BI "size_t period_sz "  ","
.BI "unsigned int periods "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dir" 12
direction of audio stream
.IP "ac" 12
audio client instanace
.IP "phys" 12
physical address that needs mapping.
.IP "period_sz" 12
audio period size
.IP "periods" 12
number of periods
.SH "RETURN"
Will be an negative value on failure or zero on success
